info.description:
This application serves main Loadero's endpoints that can be used to
manipulate test data and other services
info.title: Loadero Controller

post.description: This endpoint registers new account with given properties.

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves current account info. Account must be
registered

post.description:
This endpoint reset account password. Account must exist before. Reset is
performed based on given email. If reset password token has not been
provided then an email will be sent out.

get.description: This endpoint retrieves account info. account must be registered

put.description:
This endpoint updates account information with given properties. Account
must be previously created. Update is performed based on account ID in
path

delete.description:
This endpoint deletes account. Account must exist before. Delete is
performed based on account id and password

parameters.description: XConfirmPassword contains request sender password inside header parameter
parameters.name: X-Confirm-Password

get.description: This endpoint retrieves account avatar. Account must be registered

put.description: This endpoint sets account avatar. Account must be registered.

delete.description: This endpoint deletes account avatar. Account must be registered

get.description: This endpoint retrieves all project info.
get.summary: Get all existing projects for account

post.description:
This endpoint creates new project with given properties. If project is
created by logged in account, that account is automatically added to
project

get.description: This endpoint retrieves project info. Project must be previously created

put.description:
This endpoint updates project with given properties. Project must be
previously created

delete.description: This endpoint deletes project. Project must be previously created

post.description: This endpoint registers new aws info with given properties.

get.description: This endpoint retrieves aws info information.

put.description: This endpoint updates aws info with given properties.

delete.description: This endpoint deletes aws info entry.

post.description: This endpoint links AWS info to provided project.
post.summary: Link existing AWS info to project.

delete.description: This endpoint unlinks project from AWS info.
delete.summary: Unlink existing project from AWS info.

get.description: This endpoint retrieves file info.

This endpoint retrieves all project member info. Project must be
previously created
get.summary: Get all existing members for project

post.description:
This endpoint creates new project member or project invited member.
Project must be previously created
post.summary:
Create new member if account with specified email exists, otherwise will
create new invited member and send email notification

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves all invited project member info. Project must be
previously created
get.summary: Get all existing invited members for project

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves invited project member info. Invited member and
project must be previously created

put.description:
This endpoint updates invited project member with given properties.
Project and invited project member must be previously created

delete.description:
This endpoint deletes invited project member. Project and invited project
member must be previously created

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves project member info. Member and project must be
previously created

put.description:
This endpoint updates project member with given properties. Project and
project member must be previously created

delete.description:
This endpoint deletes project member. Project and project member
must be previously created

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves all test run info. Project must be previously
created
get.summary: Get all existing test runs for project

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves project test run info. Project and run must
be previously created
This endpoint retrieves all project run participant info.
get.summary: Get all existing project run participants for run

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves project run participant info. Run, run
participant must be previously created

This endpoint retrieves all project run results. Project, run must be
previously created and run has to be finished in order to get results

This endpoint retrieves all project result statisctics. Project and run
must be previously created

This endpoint retrieves single project run result info. Project, run and
result must be previously created

post.description: This endpoint creates subscription for project.

get.description: This endpoint retrieves subscription data.

put.description:
This endpoint updates subscription with given properties. Project and
Subscription must be previously created.

delete.description:
This endpoint deletes subscription. Project and Subscription must be
previously created

get.description: This endpoint retrieves all test info. Project must be previously created
get.summary: Get all existing tests for project

post.description: This endpoint creates new test with given data.

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves test info. Project and test must be previously
created

put.description:
This endpoint updates test with given properties. Project and test must
be previously created

delete.description: This endpoint deletes test. Project and test must be previously created

get.description: This endpoint retrieves all assert info. Test must be previously created
get.summary: Get all existing asserts for test

post.description: This endpoint creates new assert with given data.

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves assert info. Test and assert must be previously
created

put.description:
This endpoint updates assert with given properties. Test and assert must
be previously created

delete.description: This endpoint deletes assert. Test and assert must be previously created

post.description:
This endpoint duplicates given assert. Test and assert must be previously
created.

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves all assert precodndition info. Assert must be
previously created
get.summary: Get all existing assert preconditions for assert

post.description: This endpoint creates new assert precondition with given data.

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves assert precondition info. Assert and precondition
must be previously created

put.description:
This endpoint updates assert precondition with given properties. Assert
and precondition must be previously created

delete.description:
This endpoint deletes assert precondition. Assert and precondition must
be previously created

post.description:
This endpoint duplicates given test. If no copy name is provided an
"Copy of" prefix will be applied to the test name. Project and test must
be previously created.

get.description: This endpoint retrieves all group info. Test must be previously created
get.summary: Get all existing groups for test

post.description: This endpoint creates new group with given data.

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves group info. Test and group must be previously
created

put.description:
This endpoint updates group with given properties. Test and group must
be previously created

delete.description: This endpoint deletes group. Test and group must be previously created

post.description:
This endpoint duplicates given group. If no copy name is provided an
"Copy of" prefix will be applied to the group name. Test and group must
be previously created.

get.description: This endpoint retrieves all group participant info.
get.summary: Get all existing group participants for group.

post.description: This endpoint creates new group participant with given properties.

get.description: This endpoint retrieves group participant info.

put.description: This endpoint updates group participant with given properties.

post.description:
This endpoint duplicates given group participant. If no copy name is
provided an "Copy of" prefix will be applied to the participant name.

get.description: This endpoint retrieves all participant info.
get.summary: Get all existing participants for test.

post.description: This endpoint creates new participant with given properties.

get.description: This endpoint retrieves participant info.

put.description: This endpoint updates participant with given properties.

post.description:
This endpoint duplicates given participant. If no copy name is provided
an "Copy of" prefix will be applied to the participant name. Group and
participant must be previously created.

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves all test run info. Project and test must be
previously created
get.summary: Get all existing test runs for test

post.description:
This endpoint starts test execution. Project and test must be previously
created
post.summary: Create and launch new test run

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves test run info. Project, test and run must be
previously created
This endpoint retrieves all test run participant info.
get.summary: Get all existing test run participants for run

get.description:
This endpoint retrieves test run participant info. Run, run participant
must be previously created

This endpoint retrieves all test run results. Project, test, run must be
previously created and run has to be finished in order to get results

This endpoint retrieves all test result statisctics. Project, test and
run must be previously created

This endpoint retrieves single test run result info. Project, test, run
and result must be previously created

post.description:
This endpoint stops test run. Project, test and run must be
previously created. Test run needs to be in progress.

AWSInfo.title: AWSInfo describes single aws info instance with JSON field descriptions.

AWSState.description:
AWSState is concrete classificator value that is used to describe different
AWS state values. AWS state indicates current status regarding custom AWS
setup.

Account.title: Account describes single account instance with JSON field descriptions.

ArtifactInfo.title: ArtifactInfo contains single artifact type artifact URLs for single result.

ArtifactsInfo.description:
ArtifactsInfo contains all artifact URLs from single result for each
corresponding artifact type. If error was present for a artifact type then
URL paths for that artifact will be empty.

Assert.title: Assert describes single assert instance with JSON field descriptions.

AssertPrecondition.description:
AssertPrecondition describes single assert precondition instance with JSON
field descriptions.

AssertStatus.description:
AssertStatus is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe
different assert status values. Assert status indicates the final outcome of
a single assert instance.

BaseClassificator.description:
BaseClassificator is exported wrapper for generic classificator type. This
type should be used only to further extend capabilities of a classificator,
and not used directly. In those cases prefer to use Classificator interface.

Browser.description:
Browser is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe different
browser values. Browser lists currently supported browser types with
currently supported versions.

ClassificatorType.title: ClassificatorType is grouping of classificators by their represented values.

Common.title: Common describes generic assert fields that are used in other assert types.

ComputeUnit.description:
ComputeUnit is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe
different compute unit values. Compute unit lists currently supported compute
unit types used in Loadero tests.

ComputeUnitUsage.title: ComputeUnitUsage describes compute unit usage for a single project.

ErrorResponse.title: ErrorResponse will be sent in case an error occurs during request processing.

ExtendedResult.title: ExtendedResult describes single result instance with JSON field descriptions.

File.title: File describes single file instance with JSON field descriptions.

Generic.title: Generic describes generic struct fields that are used in almost all types.

Group.title: Group describes single test group instance with JSON field descriptions.

GroupParticipantBody.title: GroupParticipantBody describes single group participant instance.

IncrementStrategy.description:
IncrementStrategy is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe
different increment strategies. Increment strategy defines how users join
test rooms in order not to create DDoS attack.

InvitedMember.description:
InvitedMember describes single project invited member instance with JSON
field descriptions.

Language.description:
Language is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe
project language. Language determines which scripting language is used
to write tests within project.

MachineStats.description:
MachineStats consists of indicators about resource usage by the test
execution.

MediaType.description:
MediaType is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe
different media type values. Media types define different audio/video file
formats available to end user as a webcam/microphone feed replacements.

Member.title: Member describes single project member instance with JSON field descriptions.

MemberRole.description:
MemberRole is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe
different member role values. Member roles are different values that are
assigned to each project member. They follow a predefined hierarchy that
allows to define permissions to each member in a project.

MetricPath.description:
MetricPath defines joint path of different metric keys that lead to specific
metric. Single metric path can have multiple children, forming a tree.

NetworkParams.title: NetworkParams describes single inbound/outbound network type data.

NetworkStatistics.description:
NetworkStatistics describes inbound/outbound network type statistics
data.

NewPassword.description:
NewPassword holds fields for new account password creation.Model is used for
parsing incoming request for new account creation with account password.

Operator.description:
Operator is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe different
math operator values. Operator is mainly used in assertions to compare
values. This classificator refers to mathematical operators.

Overview.description:
Overview describes single result overview instance with JSON field
descriptions.

Pagination.title: Pagination describes information about limited response to resource requests.

Params.title: Params contains various necessary classificator fields.

Project.title: Project describes single project instance with JSON field descriptions.

Property.description:
Property is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe different
property values.

Result.title: Result describes single result instance with JSON field descriptions.

ResultAssert.description:
ResultAssert describes single result assert instance with JSON field
descriptions.

ResultLog.title: ResultLog describes single result log instance with JSON field descriptions.

ResultResourceUsage.description:
ResultResourceUsage describes single result resource usage instance with JSON
field descriptions.

ResultStatus.description:
ResultStatus is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe
different result status values. Result status indicates the final outcome of
a single result instance.

Run.title: Run describes single run instance with JSON field descriptions.

RunAssertPrecondition.description:
RunAssertPrecondition describes single run assert precondition instance with
JSON field descriptions.

RunBody.title: Body describes single run instance with JSON field descriptions.

RunParticipant.description:
RunParticipant describes single run participant instance with JSON field
descriptions.
swagger: model

RunParticipantBody.description:
Body describes single run participant instance with JSON field
descriptions.

RunStatus.description:
RunStatus is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe
different run status values. Run status indicates current state of a single
test run.

Statistics.description:
Statistics describes result resource usage statistics with JSON field
descriptions.

Subscription.description:
Subscription describes single subscription instance with JSON field
descriptions.

Test.title: Test describes single test instance with JSON field descriptions.

TestMode.description:
TestMode is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe different
test mode values. Test mode determines different logical parts of the test
such as log collection logic and different service limits.

UpdateUserBody.description:
UpdateUserBody describes the information needed for update account auth
request.

ValidationResponse.title: ValidationResponse will be sent in case a validation fails.

VideoFeed.description:
VideoFeed is a concrete classificator value that is used to describe
different video feed values. Video feed indicates the currently supported
video values.

awsInfoReponse.description:
AWSInfoReponse is response format that contains linked projects info and
AWSInfo corresponding to query.

fullProject.description:
fullProject describes single project instance with JSON field descriptions
and additional subscription info.

AssertsResponse is response format that contains pagination info and

emptyResponse.description: EmptyResponse will be sent in case there is no data to return to user.

errorResponse.description: errorResponse will be sent in case an error occurs during request processing.

fileResponse.description: FileResponse is response format that contains a avatar image file

forbiddenResponse.description:
ForbiddenResponse will be sent in case user lacks permission to access
requested resource.

groupsResponse.description:
GroupsResponse is response format that contains pagination info and

invitedMembersResponse.description:
InvitedMembersResponse is response format that contains pagination info
and results corresponding to query

membersResponse.description:
MembersResponse is response format that contains pagination info and

metricPathsResponse.description: MetricPathsResponse is list of available metric paths

participantsResponse.description:
ParticipantsResponse is response format that contains pagination info and
results corresponding to query

preconditionsResponse.description:
PreconditionResponse is response format that contains pagination info
and results corresponding to query

projectsResponse.description:
ProjectsResponse is response format that contains pagination info and
results corresponding to query

runParticipantResponse.description:
RunParticipantResponse is response format that contains pagination info
and results corresponding to query

runResultResponse.description:
RunResultResponse is response format that contains pagination info and
results corresponding to query

runsResponse.description:
RunsResponse is response format that contains pagination info and results
corresponding to query

staticTypesResponse.description:
StaticTypesResponse is response format that contains all static type
information

staticsResponse.description:
StaticsResponse is response format that contains all static resource
information

statisticsResponse.description:
StatisticsResponse is response format that contains assert overview and
machine statistics

testsResponse.description:
TestsResponse is response format that contains pagination info and
results corresponding to query

unauthorizedResponse.description:
UnauthorizedResponse will be sent in case an authorization error occurs
and user is not authorized to access requested resource.
